INTRODUCE: Let others learn your character's name

On AetherMUD, characters do not automatically know each other's names.
A stranger appears as their race description until you have been
formally introduced.

WHY STRANGERS SHOW AS RACE DESCRIPTIONS
  A human you have not met appears as "a human" or similar.
  A D-Bee appears as their race type.
  Their actual name is unknown to your character until introduced.

COMMAND
  introduce             introduces yourself to people in the room

When you introduce yourself, everyone in the room learns your name
(and you learn theirs if they are present and interactive).  After
introduction, the person appears by name in all subsequent
interactions.

ROLEPLAY NOTE
  The introduce system supports immersive roleplay.  It is considered
  polite to introduce yourself when entering a social situation.
  Some NPCs may respond differently before and after introduction.

